        <abstract> 
<p>Does not believe any organic being is evidence of design; refers GEM to the last pages of <hi rend="italic">Variation</hi> for his reasons. Even if no organism shows evidence of design, this does not preclude faith in the existence of a loving creator; evidence of such a creator must be looked for outside the limits of physical science.</p> 
            <p>Thanks him for the volume on the philosophy of medicine,</p>
            <p>and asks him to convey to the Scuola Italica thanks for the great honour they have done him.</p>
        </abstract>
